  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6596.54 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-10.3B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15.1B), dealers are caught in a narrow 15-point hedging zone where they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push toward 6605. The regime flip to PIN with 911.9M total GEX and the massive GEX surge suggests dealers just flipped to long gamma, creating a strong mean-reversion setup that should keep price pinned in this tight range. Watch 6590 as the key support where dealer buying accelerates and 6605-6610 as the resistance zone where dealer selling kicks in hard.\n\nBottom line: expect tight range-bound trading between 6590-6605 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
